                      <span>2003-11-27</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>You won't be dissapointed! I had no idea that 30 years ago when I was a 14 year old child, I was being operated on by a fomer Russian Officer condemned to death in a concentration camp! What I remember is a very kind doctor/man who encouraged an Iowa boy with a cleft lip to be all he could be. It was just last year when I was grieved to find out that the doctor who gave me a new face had died. Only later did I find out and become amazed at all he had gone through. I just had to buy the book, and found it VERY difficult to put down, not just because he was the man who operated on my lip/nose 30 years ago, but also because he wrote very well from a first person point of view. I only wish I had an autographed copy of his book! Rest in Peace, my friend! May the Lord richly bless you!<BR>-rickmauderer@charter.net</span>
                  
